ZH: 他侮辱了我的智商。
EN: He insulted my intelligence.

ZH: 她是个很善良的女孩，不会侮辱别人。
EN: She is a kind girl and she would never insult anyone.

ZH: 不管别人怎么侮辱你，都不要屈服。
EN: No matter how others insult you, never give in.

ZH: 他说了很多侮辱性的话，真叫人气愤。
EN: He said a lot of insulting words, which really angered me.

ZH: 请不要侮辱他的信仰，这是他的自由。
EN: Please do not insult his beliefs, it's his freedom.

ZH: 这是对他的侮辱，我们必须为他讨回公道。
EN: This is an insult to him, we must seek justice for him.

ZH: 面对侮辱，我们一定要保持冷静。
EN: In the face of insults, we must stay calm.

ZH: 学校严禁对他人进行侮辱行为。
EN: The school strictly prohibits any acts of insult towards others.

ZH: 对他人的侮辱是没有教养的。
EN: Insulting others is uncivilized.

ZH: 他用尽了各种方法来侮辱我。
EN: He used all sorts of methods to insult me.

ZH: 在众人面前公开侮辱他是很没品的行为。
EN: Publicly insulting him in front of everyone is very disgraceful.

ZH: 他被别人侮辱后并没有生气，反而笑了起来。
EN: He didn't get angry when someone insulted him, instead, he laughed.

ZH: 这是一个对整个族群的巨大侮辱。
EN: This is a huge insult to the entire community.

ZH: 侮辱别人只会让自己失去尊严。
EN: Insulting others will only make you lose your dignity.

ZH: 他的侮辱言行引起了众人的不满。
EN: His insulting words and actions have caused dissatisfaction among the crowd.

ZH: 我们应该努力避免侮辱他人的行为。
EN: We should strive to avoid any acts of insulting others.

ZH: 那个人喜欢侮辱弱势群体，真是太可恶了。
EN: That person enjoys insulting vulnerable groups, it's really despicable.

ZH: 种族侮辱是绝对不能容忍的。
EN: Racial insults are absolutely unacceptable.

ZH: 那些侮辱性的言论应该受到法律的制裁。
EN: Those insulting remarks should be dealt with by the law.

ZH: 他在朋友面前公开侮辱了我，我感到非常伤心。
EN: He openly insulted me in front of my friends, and I feel very hurt.
